   <head>Libellus ad Lectorem.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <seg rend="decorInit">N</seg>Il moror aut laudes, leuis aut conuitia vulgi.</l>
      <l>Pulchrum est vel doct is, vel placuisse piis.</l>
      <l>Spe quo{que} maius erit nubi si cōtingat vtrū{que}:</l>
      <l>cui <hi>Christus</hi> sapit, huic si placco, bene habet.</l>
      <l>Magnificas Domini sonitat mea linea lau<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>des,</l>
      <l>multorum lugens crimina multa virum.</l>
      <l>Fronte legas hilari, <hi>Lector,</hi> mecum{que} precare</l>
      <l>coelesti faustus detur in arce locus.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>A. N.</signed>
